notes on elisp/emacs config

* use same init.el across systems
- understand contents of .emacs.d
- combine contents of my .emacs and init.el from Lenovo Linux and
  Windows
  - set package repository sources depending on hostname
- add elpa-mirror directory to .gitignore
- version control ~/.emacs.d/
  - remote on bitbucket (currently old version)

* some elisp blocks

use Babel to include elisp blocks 
http://orgmode.org/worg/org-contrib/babel/intro.html

#+begin_src elisp
(system-name)
(string-equal (system-name) "L1MYB00L4")
system-type
(cond
 ((string-equal system-type "windows-nt")
  (progn
    (message "MS Windows")))
 ((string-equal system-type "gnu/linux")
  (progn
    (message "Linux"))))
#+end_src

#+RESULTS:
: MS Windows

How to determine OS version
http://ergoemacs.org/emacs/elisp_determine_OS_version.html


